   <h1>Re: [T2]  New Microbus ( S A V W )</h1>
   <b>myangelmorgan_at_juno_dot_com</b><br/>
   <i>2002-08-22 03:40:53+00</i><br/>
   <br/>
   <pre>On Wed, 21 Aug 2002 11:38:33 -0700 "ronnie chase"
<ronniechase_at_worldnet.att_dot_net> writes:
> As a toyota driver I find that highly offensive:)
> 
> If you took the NEW Microbus parked it in a lot and asked
> > people what it was they would probally say Toyota. We know what it 
is only
> > because we have followed it from Concept.
-------LMAO!------------- 

On Wed, 21 Aug 2002 09:25:11 -0700 Rik <nisse_at_attbi_dot_com> writes:
> >At 10:08 AM 8/21/2002 -0500, Doug wrote:
> >... Bus owners have always been viewed as Hippies and losers,
> >now is a good chance to show we are normal everyday people who just 
love the
> >old buses.
> Hey!  Watch it bub!  "normal"? "everyday people"?  Them's fightin' 
words!
>  ...........I'll be over here, sittin' under the tree, with all the 
> Hippies and losers-- thankyahverymuch!
---------SAVE ME A SPACE!!!---------

On Wed, 21 Aug 2002 10:28:04 -0500 "dougz2" <dougz2_at_msn_dot_com> writes:
> so whats next for the copy cats at the "new" VW? a retro Ghia?
----------ever compare the ghia to the audi t4? coincidence? i think
not... lol, just kidding. i think it looks as much like the ghia as the
new beetle looks like the original beetle.

On Wed, 21 Aug 2002 12:14:25 -0700 "B R M" <jezzina_at_ctc_dot_net> writes:
> Nope , Ghia is a trademark of the ford motor company.
--------WHAT???---------

> I would love to have a EV doublecab or singlecab. 
---------this is a good point... even the vanagon had a "truck" version,
didnt it? i hadnt thought of that..
 
> The fact that our busses are going on 30
> years and older is what gives us that feeling, the fact that our busses
have
> seen things that we can only imagine.They get more charater as they 
> get older ,more personallity and fewer people will be able to remember 
> when they were new adding a whole new mistique about them . 
--------excellent point... i think their age DOES have something to do
with their character, and it is sad to think of a day when no one can
tell younger people what it was like to own a brand new splitty, bay
window or even vanagon... *tear*

> This is something the new bus doesnt have but eventually will have in
40 years.
--------unfortunately, i dont believe ANY car made today will be around
in 40 years. i hate to say it, but "they just dont make 'em like they
used to!!!"
 
> When the new bus drivers wave and honk i will just wave back 
> politely and go on my merry way , in my old bus.
--------why would they wave? new beetle owners dont wave, regardless of
the retro image they were going for. well, not in these neck of the
woods, anyway...</pre>


